  <title>mongoc_collection_set_read_concern()</title>

  <section id="synopsis">
    <title>Synopsis</title>
    <synopsis><code mime="text/x-csrc"><![CDATA[void
mongoc_collection_set_read_concern (mongoc_collection_t          *collection,
                                    const mongoc_read_concern_t  *read_concern);
]]></code></synopsis>
  </section>

  <section id="parameters">
    <title>Parameters</title>
    <table>
      <tr><td><p>collection</p></td><td><p>A <code xref="mongoc_collection_t">mongoc_collection_t</code>.</p></td></tr>
      <tr><td><p>read_concern</p></td><td><p>A <code xref="mongoc_read_concern_t">mongoc_read_concern_t</code>.</p></td></tr>
    </table>
  </section>

  <section id="description">
    <title>Description</title>
    <p>Sets the read concern to use for operations on <code>collection</code>.</p>
    <p>The default read concern is empty: No readConcern is sent to the server unless explicitly configured.</p>
  </section>

